&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp If Thorfinn is still with you, tell him what I've told you.  If you need me, let me know.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Don't screw up.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp -- Kelthana</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Thorfinn grunted.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Trying to remember how to read?<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Very funny,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I signaled back.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> It's a message from Kelthana, about a new group in Highpass and some connection they have with Vilnius.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Suddenly, something clicked into place in my mind.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> But,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I signaled slowly, I think there's more afoot here than she knows.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Oh?[/i]  He cracked his neck unconcernedly.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kelthana says the leader of this group is a man called &quot;Anson McBale&quot;,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  I signaled, my white brows furrowing over my gold-flecked eyes.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Does that name sound odd to you?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  He looked at me blankly, and I continued.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Antonius Bayle - AnSON MCBale.  The son of Bayle, or of Qeynos, depending on how you want to interpret it.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Thorfinn scratched at his beard.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> What does that have to do with anything?<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It's a message to us, or to whoever were to get ahold of the pouch before Vilnius,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I replied.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> It's letting us know that we should take the pouch to its source.  Whoever this &quot;Anson McBale&quot; is, I'm betting it's this pouch he wants.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp And if you're wrong?  If his name is just some sort of unfortunate coincidence?  </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->My teacher tapped his toe impatiently.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> If that's the case,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I signaled with a sigh, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> it won't make much of a difference anyway.  We can be back here within three days, to deliver the pouch to Vilnius as we promised, and long before Malka Rale comes out of hiding to let Vilnius know we succeeded.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp My teacher pondered for a moment, tapping his toe.  With a shrug, I left him to his deliberations; either he'd agree with me, or he wouldn't, and no coercing on my part was going to make any difference.  With the help of a flint-and-tinder, I set Kelthana's parchment on fire, then backed away, covering my nose and mouth with my cloak as it slowly curled into a blackening ball of ash.  The smell of the burning Iron Dimethy powder was awful.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp After a long moment, Thorfinn nodded.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> All right - we'll try it your way, and see how it plays out.  Vilnius certainly hasn't given me any motive to trust him.  But you realize, this will mean Malka Rale won't get paid either.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp If I'm right, that means that Vilnius never had any intention of paying her anyway,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I replied without any hesitation.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> She'd deliver the pouch, and he'd disappear.  At least this way, she'll have a decent chance of getting away from Hanns' men.  Vilnius, on the other hand, she'll have to deal with on her own.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Thorfinn shrugged.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Whatever you say.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Without another gesture, he turned on his heel and started off into the East, striding into the gathering dawn like a man walking into a strong wind.  I followed silently, clenching my fist around a handful of my cloak with frustration.  I hated uncertainty.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Behind me, I heard the crackle of dying flames as the parchment finally burned out.  A swirl of ash dusted the wind, and I closed my eyes.  It would be winter soon.  <p><b> -- Baron Arafain Entreri, 60 Assassin<br> -- Arafein Soulstriker, 54 Champion Relic<br> -- Arafax Kokorozan, 20 Monk Giantfriend<br> -- Requiem of Souls<br> -- Formerly of The Rathe Server, now of Zebuxoruk<br></b><i>"Once, in the old west, a gentleman shot a professional gunfighter in the back. When asked why he didn't give the other chap a chance to draw, he replied, 'Well, he's dead and I'm alive and that's how I wanted it to be." -- from <u>Red Planet</u>, Robert A. Heinlein</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugaenashadowdweller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaena Shadowdweller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 1:40:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=871.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragebringer Novella - Part 1</span><hr size=1> very nice... please continue   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utrolojesterkinng.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trolo Jesterkinng</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 8:32:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=871.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pictureshost.homestead.com/files/pikachu.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top a